  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NGO Support / Bridgeit Tanzania</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Tanzanian schools are poorly equipped, with many lacking electricity and basic infrastructure, lab equipment and textbooks. Primary school teachers receive minimal support and training and lack sufficient skills and resources to engage young people. The Teacher Training College (TTC) Bridgeit program will train professors and student teachers in 2 teacher training colleges on participatory and gender-responsive teaching methods, with particular focus on mathematics, science and life skills. The project seeks to build the capacity of  the Tanzanian Ministry of Education and Vocational Training (MoEVT) and institutionalize the Bridgeit training and methodologies into the pre-service teacher training.</narrative>
  </description>
